Package org.fluentjdbc

Class DatabaseBulkInsertBuilder<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fluentjdbc.DatabaseBulkInsertBuilder<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DatabaseBulkUpdatable<T,​DatabaseBulkInsertBuilder<T>>
    public class DatabaseBulkInsertBuilder<T>
extends Object
implements DatabaseBulkUpdatable<T,​DatabaseBulkInsertBuilder<T>>
    Fluently generate a INSERT ... statement for a list of objects. Crate with a list of object and use setField(String, Function) to pass in a function that will be called for each object in the list. Use generatePrimaryKeys(String, BiConsumer) to use the return value from the underlying database table autogeneration of keys.

    Example:

         public void insertAll(List<TagType> tagTypes, Connection connection) {
         tagTypesTable.bulkInsert(tagTypes)
             .setField("name", TagType::getName)
             .generatePrimaryKeys("id", TagType::setId)
             .execute(connection);
     }
